<paragraph blockId="35.[189,1399,315,378]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
The endocarp was considered “smooth inside” (
<bibRefCitation author="Sleumer H." box="[753,924,315,341]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 87" refId="ref61319" refString="Sleumer H. 1971. Icacinaceae. In: van Steenis C. G. G. J. (ed.) Flora Malesiana. Vol. 7 (1): 1 - 87. Noordhoff, Leiden." type="journal article" year="1971">Sleumer 1971</bibRefCitation>
). Here we demonstrate that the locule is densely covered by papillae. These papillae are difficult to observe without SEM.
</paragraph>
